  "title": "A Stray Cat Stole the Show at Romeo and Juliet",
  "script": "Who invited this cat? A touring production of Romeo and Juliet in Izmir, Turkey, was going exactly as planned — until a ginger stray wandered onstage during the tragic final scene. Romeo was lying there, dramatically dying. The cat sat beside him. Licked his hair. Batted at his arm. The audience lost it. The dancer stayed in character — because what else do you do? — while the cat sprawled out and started grooming itself next to the 'corpse.' At curtain call, the cat took a bow. Videos went viral within hours — 8 million views combined. The Imperial Russian Ballet Company kept their dignity. The stray kept the stage. So: when does Juliet's cat get a contract?",
